Model Accuracy: 0.95
Prediction for New Data
 
Input: Age = 22, Salary = 40000  
Output: 0 (No Purchase)
💡 Notes
Ensure car_purchase_data.csv is in the same directory as the script.
The model uses 80% training data and 20% testing data.
The K-value (neighbors) is set to 5 using the Euclidean distance metric (p=2).
The confusion matrix evaluates the performance of the model.
📌 Next Steps
Tune hyperparameters (K-value, metric, weights) for better accuracy.
Try different classification algorithms (SVM, Decision Tree, Random Forest).
Deploy the model using Flask or Streamlit for real-time predictions.
